  "text": "We can only speculate about why the ATQ and DAS had dissimilar relations with depression severity. Although both measures tend to covary with depression severity in treatment trials, [CITATION_1] the DAS demonstrates greater stability over time. [CITATION_2] One reason may be that on the DAS, respondents are asked to describe the way they think most of the time, whereas on the ATQ individuals indicate how often the thought occurred to them over the last week. Next, the DAS items form 2 factors: perfectionism and need for approval. [CITATION_3] It may be that for people living with TBI, issues around self-criticism,",
